      "rationale": "Construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are the primary QoIs specified in ASTM F1717 and are directly relevant to the clinical performance of pedicle screw constructs under physiological bending loads. These QoIs are accepted by FDA as appropriate metrics for structural performance assessment of spinal implant systems."
